---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Divorce Involving a Business in Maryland | Business Valuation & Division | Child Custody with a Plan"
  description="When a business is part of your Maryland divorce, you need attorneys who understand business valuation, buyout structures, and co-ownership options. Call (301) 289-8917."
  ogTitle="Maryland Divorce Involving Businesses | Child Custody with a Plan"
  ogDescription="Protect your business in a Maryland divorce. Expert guidance on business valuation, buyouts, and co-ownership. Rockville & Baltimore divorce attorneys."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 bg-[url('/grid.svg')] bg-repeat"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-[#D4A843] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Business & Divorce</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-5">
        Divorces Involving<br class="hidden md:block" /> a Business
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/80 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Your business is more than an asset — it's your livelihood, your legacy, and in many cases, your most complex marital property. We protect what you've built.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-[#D4A843] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#b8902f] transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:3012898917" class="border-2 border-white text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-[#0D6E6E] transition-colors">
          (301) 289-8917
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <div class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-3">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-[#0D6E6E]">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/divorce" class="hover:text-[#0D6E6E]">Divorce</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-800 font-medium">Divorces Involving Businesses</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-5">When Your Business Is on the Line</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Business-related divorces are among the most legally and financially complex cases in Maryland family law. Whether you're the business owner seeking to protect your company, or the non-owner spouse seeking fair recognition of your contributions, the stakes are enormous.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Maryland courts must first determine whether a business — or a portion of it — constitutes marital property. If it does, the court must then determine its value and how to address it within the overall property settlement.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            Our attorneys have direct experience handling high-asset divorce cases involving business interests, working alongside certified business valuators, forensic accountants, and financial experts to present the strongest possible case on your behalf.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-[#D4A843] rounded-lg p-5">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Is My Business Marital Property?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">It depends on timing, ownership structure, and how marital funds were used. Businesses started before marriage may still have a marital component if they grew significantly during the marriage using marital resources or effort. We analyze every angle.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-[#0D6E6E]/5 border border-[#0D6E6E]/20 rounded-lg p-5">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Business Types We Handle</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
              {[
                "Sole proprietorships and partnerships",
                "LLCs and S-corps",
                "Medical, dental, and professional practices",
                "Restaurants and retail businesses",
                "Real estate holding companies",
                "Startups and technology companies",
                "Family-owned businesses",
                "Franchise operations"
              ].map(type => (
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
                  <span class="text-[#D4A843]">•</span>
                  {type}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Business Valuation -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-3">Business Valuation in Divorce</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Accurate valuation is the cornerstone of any business divorce. The value of a business can vary dramatically depending on which method is used — and we know how to navigate this.</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-10">
        {[
          {
            method: "Income Approach",
            desc: "Values the business based on its earning capacity — typically using discounted cash flow analysis. Often favored for service businesses and professional practices.",
            icon: "📊"
          },
          {
            method: "Market Approach",
            desc: "Compares the business to similar companies that have recently sold. Works best for businesses with accessible market comparables.",
            icon: "📈"
          },
          {
            method: "Asset Approach",
            desc: "Values the business based on net tangible assets — useful for asset-heavy businesses like real estate holding companies.",
            icon: "🏢"
          }
        ].map(v => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
            <div class="text-4xl mb-4">{v.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#0D6E6E] mb-3">{v.method}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">{v.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">What Affects Valuation in Divorce?</h3>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            "Goodwill — personal vs. enterprise distinction (critical in MD)",
            "Owner's compensation relative to market rate",
            "Pending contracts, accounts receivable, and liabilities",
            "Minority interest discounts and marketability discounts",
            "Revenue trends and client concentration risk",
            "Hidden perks and lifestyle expenses run through the business"
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-[#D4A843] font-bold mt-0.5">→</span>
              <span class="text-white/90 text-sm">{item}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Resolution Options -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-3">Options for Resolving Business Interests</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">There's no single "right" answer for dividing a business in divorce. We help you understand every available option and advocate for the one that best serves your interests.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            option: "Buyout",
            icon: "💰",
            desc: "The business-owning spouse buys out the other spouse's interest — often by trading other marital assets (e.g., retirement accounts, the marital home) or through structured payments.",
            pros: "Clean break; owner retains full control",
            cons: "Requires liquidity or offset assets"
          },
          {
            option: "Sale of Business",
            icon: "🤝",
            desc: "Both spouses agree to sell the business and divide the net proceeds. May be the only option when neither party can afford a buyout.",
            pros: "Both spouses share in proceeds equally",
            cons: "Disrupts operations; may depress sale price under time pressure"
          },
          {
            option: "Co-Ownership",
            icon: "⚖️",
            desc: "Both spouses retain ownership of the business post-divorce, operating under a structured agreement. Rare but viable when both parties have active roles.",
            pros: "Preserves business continuity and value",
            cons: "Requires strong post-divorce communication and legal safeguards"
          },
          {
            option: "Negotiated Settlement",
            icon: "📝",
            desc: "Business value is incorporated into the overall marital settlement — the non-owner spouse receives other assets of equivalent value in exchange for waiving claims to the business.",
            pros: "Flexible; avoids disruption to the business",
            cons: "Requires accurate valuation for equitable trade-off"
          }
        ].map(opt => (
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-100">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <span class="text-3xl">{opt.icon}</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">{opt.option}</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">{opt.desc}</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-xs">
              <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-2">
                <p class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-1">Advantage</p>
                <p class="text-green-600">{opt.pros}</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-2">
                <p class="font-semibold text-red-700 mb-1">Consideration</p>
                <p class="text-red-600">{opt.cons}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Protecting Business Owner -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#0D6E6E]">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div class="text-white">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">If You Own the Business</h2>
          <p class="text-white/80 mb-4">Your goal is to protect your ownership interests, preserve operational continuity, and limit the business's exposure in the divorce settlement.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              "Challenge the characterization of business growth as marital",
              "Distinguish personal goodwill from enterprise goodwill",
              "Obtain independent valuation from a qualified expert",
              "Structure buyout or offset arrangements that avoid disruption",
              "Protect confidential business information during litigation",
              "Ensure no court orders interfere with day-to-day operations"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-white/90 text-sm">
                <span class="text-[#D4A843] font-bold mt-0.5">✓</span>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="text-white">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">If Your Spouse Owns the Business</h2>
          <p class="text-white/80 mb-4">You may have significant rights to the business — especially if you contributed to its growth, supported your spouse's career, or if marital funds were invested in it.</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              "Demand full financial disclosure of business records",
              "Subpoena bank statements, tax returns, and financial statements",
              "Challenge artificially low valuations from your spouse's expert",
              "Identify personal expenses hidden within business accounts",
              "Quantify your direct and indirect contributions to growth",
              "Ensure your equitable share of appreciated value is recognized"
            ].map(item => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-white/90 text-sm">
                <span class="text-[#D4A843] font-bold mt-0.5">✓</span>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Protect Your Business in Divorce</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Business divorces require specialized legal knowledge and a clear strategic plan. Schedule a free consultation with our Maryland divorce attorneys today.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#0a5a5a] transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:3012898917" class="bg-[#D4A843] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#b8902f] transition-colors">
          Call (301) 289-8917
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">Rockville: 100 Park Ave Suite 205 · Baltimore: 1537 Light St #100 · Mon–Fri 9AM–9PM</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
